<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="323" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1384,2030]" pageId="6" pageNumber="323">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,1384,1410]" pageId="6" pageNumber="323">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
An 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Croissandeau" authorityYear="1891" box="[329,479,1385,1410]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Entomoculia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="323" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[329,479,1385,1410]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="323">Entomoculia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ascribable to the nominal subgenus for its robust build, the presence of chitinized thickenings on the male genital segment and for the characters of the male and female genitalia; welldifferentiated from its congeners by the conformation of the aedeagus and female copulatory plates.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
